products.description:
Inspired by one of Jay Chou’s albums, Eight Degrees Taiwanese Bistro provides food enthusiasts with a variety of Taiwanese dishes and snacks prepared by experienced chefs. Choose from their wide menu selection ranging from popular Taiwanese street snacks and bubble tea to staple meals and unique desserts or opt for a taste of their signature Taiwanese oyster omelette or salted crispy chicken.

Diners can have their pick of belly-friendly dishes such as homemade XO sauce wok-fried chee cheong fun and deep fried prawn balls with hawthorn sauce. Other homely selections include five-spice fries with cheese, century egg tofu with pork floss, and sakura shrimp fried rice with pork floss.

company.description: Curry fish head is their signature here, besides the flavoursome spices, the price is fairly reasonable for a full fish head and one of the dishes you should not missed at Curry & Curry. Other dishes worthwhile to explore include the fried bitter gourd with eggs, Rendang Chicken.
